The paper deals with online learning in misspecified linear stochastic multi-armed bandit problems, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the performance of linear bandit algorithms in the presence of misspecification, which is a problem that is relevant to the subfield of reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also involves the use of hypothesis testing and decision-making algorithms, which are relevant to the subfields of data science (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
